# Beacon Conventions

- Use TypeScript everywhere; avoid the `any` type. Prefer explicit types, generics, or `unknown` with narrowing when the type is not known.
- Every function gets a short comment explaining what it does.
- When you create a function, also create a matching test.
- Keep functions small and readable; extract helpers when logic grows beyond a single clear responsibility.
